properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 28 at 4:59AM PST until January 28 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...HIGH ELEVATION SNOW TONIGHT THROUGH TOMORROW...

.A storm system currently impacting the region is bringing rain
and high elevation snow this morning to the Washington Cascades
and the northern Blue Mountains. It will continue into the
afternoon and then dissipate by evening.

* WHAT...Moderate snow expected in Western Kittitas county from
near Cle Elum up towards Snoqualmie Pass below 3000 feet. Total
snow accumulations of up to 7 inches, more above 3000 feet.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the Washington Cascades.

* WHEN...From now through 10 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING BELOW 3000 FEET
